There they are, down on their knees, looking at this goddamn map.

54:43.737 --> 54:46.860
Whoa, oh, that's what it's like.

54:47.361 --> 54:54.928
You can hope this book connects with

54:56.917 --> 55:00.562
the whole environmental movement.

55:00.602 --> 55:09.233
Because this is the North American environment and what most of us think of is at its first time.

55:10.214 --> 55:15.501
And certainly that was true for Missouri and all the way to Idaho and beyond the Pacific.

55:15.521 --> 55:20.427
This is how it was.

55:23.242 --> 55:52.000
And it's fascinating to see it from the point of view of those who were living there, whether Indian or white, and trying to make a living and I guess survive in these mountains and these galleys and these plains.

55:51.980 --> 56:00.792
All of us would like to have been there.

56:01.177 --> 56:05.423
Not all of us, but some of us who desperately have loved to have been here.

